What you need to know:

The Timberwolves, who finished 19-45 in the coronavirus-disrupted 2020 season, opted for Edwards, who averaged 19 points per game as a freshman, to bolster a roster that includes young stars Karl-Anthony Towns and D'Angelo Russell.The Golden State Warriors took center James Wiseman with the second overall pick and the Charlotte Hornets -- owned by NBA icon Michael Jordan -- made guard LaMelo Ball the third selection.